Durban - The BRICS Business Council wrapped up its Durban leg of the countrywide BRICS conference with three tour visits to sites KwaZulu-Natal on Monday. 
One of the tours offered delegates a chance to walk through the Ohlange High School in Inanda, where struggle hero, Nelson Mandela, cast his very first vote as a free man back in 1994. 


 






